    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/244</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Yokohama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scidmore</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">John F. Stevens</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WD1">Daniel Willard</persName>:</p>
                <p>Your cable 17th. Think you have decided wisely that <persName corresp="#p_ECH1"
                        >Emerson</persName> and party should remain in Japan until situation clears.
                    Arrangements being made for ample credit in Japan through American Ambassador at
                    Tokyo as you request. There seems good reason to believe situation in Russia
                    will improve and that <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> in short
                    time will be given opportunity to render service originally intended. Keep us
                    fully advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
